 Soso Sobrekon a Nigerian music executive, has disputed accusations that singer Teni was kidnapped during a performance in River State. It was earlier reported that what was supposed to be a wonderful night for Teni and music fans turned into a nightmare when a gunshot disrupted the event. The Teni’s bouncers, according to an eyewitness, stopped the kidnapping attempt by firing randomly into the air. READ ALSO: Soso Soberekon Survives Ghastly Car Accident Since then, Nigerians have voiced concern for Teni’s well-being as a result of the heinous crime. However, in a response to the post on his Instagram site, music executive Soso Berekon stated that Teni’s bouncer did not fire a gunshot. He went on to say that the show was disrupted due to a fight that broke out during the event, not a kidnapping attempt. See Post Below: 